This is an example of a manifest file. It is used to declare the name, description, version number etc. of the extension.
It is also used to declare the extension behaviour and the permissions.
This file must have in JSON format.



{
  "manifest_version": 2,

  "name": "Getting started example",
  "description": "This extension shows a Google Image search result for the current page",
  "version": "1.0",

  "browser_action": {
    "default_icon": "icon.png",
    "default_popup": "popup.html"
  },
  "permissions": [
    "activeTab",
    "https://ajax.googleapis.com/"
  ]
}
